{
  "texts": [
    "The overall classification accuracy of our proposed method stands at 96.3% on the Eurosat test dataset, marking notable improvements of 7.13%, 2.15%, 2.13%, and 1.55% over Pretrained Resnet-34 on ImageNet, Pretrained Resnet-34 on ImageNet with Finetunning, MTLN, and Multi-Branch Deep Learning Framework (MBDLF), respectively.",
    "Figure 10 visually reinforces the effectiveness of our proposed strategy, achieving a satisfactory accuracy of 96.3% across 10 categories, with most categories boasting over 95% accuracy.",
    "This investigation suggests that augmenting the network's depth with additional layers may not yield a substantial performance improvement, particularly in the context of aerial images.It was additionally noted that deeper layers could prompt the network to discern features effectively in natural images, yet these deeper models exhibit suboptimal performance in aerial scenes.",
    "This observation is apparent in Table 3.",
    "The decreased performance on the EuroSAT dataset can be ascribed to its inclusion of more varied scenes and increased inter-class similarities, particularly among the herbaceous classes, annual crop, and permanent crop."
  ]
}